    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UCI procedures bug in 4-resource TDD case and debug log issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `uci_procedures` function in the eNB PHY layer had two critical bugs that could cause incorrect HARQ ACK/NACK processing and debug log failures. \n\nFirst, when processing 4 PUCCH resources in TDD mode, if `metric[3]` was determined to be the maximum among the four metrics, the code incorrectly used `pucch_b0b1[2]` values instead of `pucch_b0b1[3]` values for determining the HARQ response. This led to incorrect ACK/NACK decisions being sent to the UE.\n\nSecond, a debug log statement referenced undefined variables (`DLSCH_id`, `metric0`, `metric1`) which could cause compilation failures or runtime issues when debug logging was enabled.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the first issue:\n1. Configure a TDD eNB with 4 PUCCH resources for HARQ ACK/NACK\n2. Transmit data to a UE such that `metric[3]` becomes the maximum metric\n3. Observe incorrect HARQ ACK/NACK values being processed due to use of wrong PUCCH resource data\n\nTo reproduce the second issue:\n1. Compile with DEBUG_PHY_PROC enabled\n2. Run eNB with UCI procedures active\n3. Observe compilation errors or runtime issues due to undefined variables in debug log\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED/phy_procedures_lte_eNb.c`: \n  - Fixed incorrect comment and array indexing when `metric[3]` is the maximum in 4-resource TDD case\n  - Fixed debug log to use properly defined variables instead of undefined `DLSCH_id`, `metric0`, `metric1`\n"
}